SIMPLE: phylloxera
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phylloxera
<hw>Phyl`lox*e"ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>fy`llon</grk> leaf + <grk>xhro`s</grk> dry.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small hemipterous insect (<spn>Phylloxera
vastatrix</spn>) allied to the aphids. It attacks the roots and leaves
of the grapevine, doing great damage, especially in Europe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It exists in several forms, some of which are winged,
other wingless. One form produces galls on the leaves and twigs, another
affects the roots, causing galls or swellings, and often killing the
vine.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The diseased condition of a vine caused by the
insect just described.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phylloxeridae</ent>⟦br⟧
